overview: As the Civil War spills our nation’s blood, Capt. John Hayes (Randolph Scott) fights on a vital but little-known battlefront. He aims to ship gold to Union banks through a small Colorado town, defying Southern sympathizers who aim to stop him. At any cost. As chiseled and bone-lean as its star, Westbound is the sixth of seven Westerns Scott made with director Budd Boetticher, films that – along with the James Stewart-Anthony Mann Westerns – helped remake the genre in the 50s, substituting grit and veracity for white-hat heroics.
tagline: Hellbound for Vengeance for the Flaming Redhead Who Betrayed Him!
title: Westbound

overview: The only business in the Wild West town of Jericho that corrupt sheriff Alex Flood doesn't control behind the scenes is the stagecoach owned by tough-willed widow Molly Lang and her right-hand man, Hickman. Former marshal Dolan, recently hired by Lang and Hickman as a driver, wants to stay out of the mess, but when he sees Flood's henchman Yarbrough assault Lang, he steps up to fight the corruption.
tagline: A former deputy and a strong-willed widow determine to stop a ruthless town boss.
title: Rough Night in Jericho

overview: An upstart outlaw baits a legendary gunslinger, now a marshal in love with a saloon keeper.
title: The Last Challenge

overview: Armed with a harpoon, a Swedish whaler is out for revenge after the death of his father. A greedy oil man trying to buy up the Swede's land might be the guilty party.
tagline: When the Texas Plains Ran With Blood and Black Gold!
title: Terror in a Texas Town

overview: John Henry returns to his hometown in hopes of repairing his relationship with his estranged father, but a local gang is terrorizing the town. John Henry is the only one who can stop them, however he has abandoned both his gun and reputation as a fearless quick-draw killer.
title: Forsaken

overview: A ragtag group of gunslingers try to make their way in a post-apocalyptic world. The twist to this world is that it’s just not barren and dangerous, it’s also filled with flesh-eating zombies. The gunslingers will find themselves stranded in a town and forced to make a choice on either to save the citizens of the town or save themselves.
title: Dead 7

original_title: The Duchess and the Dirtwater Fox
overview: A female hustler is chasing after rich men, but becomes repeatedly mixed up with a suave con man and card shark through a series of misadventures before falling in love with him.
tagline: Once upon a time, If the rustlers didn't get you, the hustlers did.
title: The Duchess and the Dirtwater Fox

overview: A young couple's wedding ceremony is brutally interrupted when a pair of outlaw brothers arrive and massacre almost everyone in sight. They kidnap the beautiful young bride and leave her husband for dead. Luckily, he only sustains a flesh wound and quickly saddles up to track down the brothers before they sell his wife and a group of other women at an auction to a group of Mexican brothel owners.
tagline: 3-D! It's Back! It's Bigger! It's Better! And it's... Comin' At Ya!
title: Comin' at Ya!

overview: A satire of the Great American Way, with Lemonade Joe a "clean living" gunfighter who drinks only Kola-Loca Lemonade and convinces everyone else in town (with his gun skills) that all "real men" drink ONLY lemonade!
title: Lemonade Joe

overview: Union soldiers in search of food descend on the farm of a Confederate family and decide to stay until one in their ranks' wounds have healed. While the war weary Union captain (Chris Cooper) falls for the mother of the family (Patricia Clarkson) - whose husband is off fighting for the rebels - her son plots revenge on the dirty, double-dealing Yankees. Co-stars Kris Kristofferson.

title: Pharaoh's  Army

overview: Legendary Lawman and Gunslinger Wild Bill Hickok, is tasked with taming the wildest cow-town in the West, while delivering his own brand of frontier Justice and infamous gunfighter's reputation as the fastest draw in the West is put to the test
title: Hickok

overview: Duke Fergus falls for Ann 'Flaxen' Tarry in the Barbary Coast in turn-of-the-century San Francisco. He loses money to crooked gambler Boss Tito Morell, goes home, learns to gamble, and returns. After he makes a fortune, he opens his own place with Flaxen as the entertainer; but the 1906 quake destroys his place.
tagline: The brawling, colorful story of the queen of hearts and the ace of gamblers... with a shock climax such as the screen has never known!
title: Flame of Barbary Coast

overview: Rod Drew hunts for a missing girl and finds himself in a fight over a goldmine as well.
tagline: WHERE LIFE WAS RAW AND MIGHT WAS LAW!
title: The Trail Beyond

overview: A marshal (Al "Lash" La Rue) with a whip and a sheriff (Al "Fuzzy" St. John) with a sense of humor end a gold-mine feud.
tagline: LATEST IN THE SERIES OF SMASH ACTION WESTERNS
title: Border Feud

overview: A bounty hunter searches the west for a wanted outlaw named Red Roundtree.
title: Into the Badlands

overview: Jordan Donavan, a photographer in New York, is so disappointed when after five years of going steady Edward Morgan offers her not marriage but just to move in with him, that she accepts the match-making arranged via a magazine by her female friend with Tyler Ross, a horse rancher in the West, whose candidacy was actually also posted by his sister. After a bad start they soon grow closer.
title: Straight From the Heart

overview: Set in America's Colonial period, John Ford's adventure tale follows Gilbert (Henry Fonda) and Lana Martin (Claudette Colbert) as they try to survive the rugged frontier. After their settlement is repeatedly attacked by Indians, the couple is taken in by a spinster (Edna May Oliver). Lana bears a son, while Gilbert heads off to fight the Indians and the British. He returns, wounded, to find his family once again under attack by the Indians.
title: Drums Along the Mohawk

overview: A man comes home after serving 18 years in jail for murder in this routine western. Although the man killed in self defense, rumors in town circulated that he murdered the victim in cold blood. The ex-con wants to get his life together, but the two sons of the slain man are gunning for the man who killed their father.
title: Time to Die

overview: A man who was falsly accused for murder escapes the sheriffs and starts a new life in a town at the border of the States to Mexico. But he cannot settle in peace as his chasers are trying to find him.
tagline: DANGER SHADOWED EVERY STEP HE TOOK!
title: Face of a Fugitive

overview: A crotchety old ranch owner fights to be able to live his life the way he wants to, and not the way other people--and the law--tell him he has to.
title: Scandalous John

title: The Actress, the Dollars and the Transylvanians

overview: Noon is a gunfighter who has become amnesiac. Helped by Rimes, an outlaw who has befriended him, he tries to figure out who he is actually. It gradually appears that his wife and kid have been murdered. As time goes by, Noon also recalls a fortune hidden somewhere. Niland, a scheming judge, and Peg Cullane, a greedy will do everything to prevent Noon and Rimes from achieving their end while Fan Davidge, a woman living in a ghost town, will support them.
tagline: From The Pen Of The Greatest Western Writer In America Today -- Louis L'Amour
title: The Man Called Noon

overview: A band of renegade Apaches attempts to steal a shipment of rifles being transported to Fort Collins.
tagline: THUNDERING Out Of The Reservation! THE LAST ATTACK OF THE APACHE NATION!
title: Massacre Canyon
